   SECTION 11: LIMITATION ON CACHING

   You acknowledge that Ezoic’s Service is offered as a platform to
   optimize, cache and serve web pages and websites and is not offered for
   other purposes, such as remote storage. Accordingly, you understand and
   agree to use the Service solely for the purpose of optimizing, hosting
   and serving web pages as viewed through a web browser or other
   application and the Hypertext Markup Language (HTML) protocol or other
   equivalent technology. Ezoic’s Service is also a shared web caching
   service, which means a number of customers’ websites are cached from
   the same server. To ensure that Ezoic’s Service is reliable and
   available for the greatest number of users, a customer’s usage cannot
   adversely affect the performance of other customers’ sites.
   Additionally, the purpose of Ezoic’s Service is to proxy web content,
   not store data. Using an account primarily as an online storage space,
   including the storage or caching of a disproportionate percentage of
   pictures, movies, audio files, or other non-HTML content, is
   prohibited. You further agree that if, at Ezoic’s sole discretion, you
   are deemed to have violated this SECTION, or if Ezoic, in its sole
   discretion, deems it necessary due to excessive burden or potential
   adverse impact on Ezoic’s systems, potential adverse impact on other
   users, server processing power, server memory, abuse controls, or other
   reasons, Ezoic may suspend or terminate your account without notice to
   or liability to you.

